      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This museum-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD represents the pinnacle of rotary engineering. Power is delivered by a flawlessly maintained 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged engine, exhibiting factory-spec compression across all rotor faces. The drivetrain features a precise five-speed manual transaxle and a limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution. The chassis remains structurally pristine, retaining its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and four-piston braking system with zero fade. Finished in original paint with an unblemished interior, this specimen is free of the typical heat-cycle wear associated with the FD platform. A rare, unmolested example for the serious enthusiast seeking peak longitudinal and lateral performance.",
